<div id="centering-tab-content" class="tab-content">
  <p>Centering things used to be one of the notoriously difficult things to do in CSS. With flexbox, we can now easily center elements 
    (both horizontally and vertically!)</p>

  <div class="centering-box">
    <button>Meet me in the middle</button>
  </div>

  <p>This is achieved by setting the following properties on the container's class:</p>

  <pre>
  .centering-box {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center; /* Centers content vertically */
    justify-content: center; /* Centers content horizontally */
  }</pre>
</div>

<div id="sidebar-tab-content" class="tab-content">
  <p>The layout of the side-bar is achieved using flexbox layout as follows:</p>
  <pre>
#main-container {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row;
  height: 100vh;
}

#main-menu-bar {
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

#page-content {
  flex-grow: 1;
}
  </pre>
  <p>When the window gets resized to a smaller width, we simply set <code>flex-direction: column</code>:</p>
  <pre>
@media only screen and (max-width: 768px) {
  #main-container {
    flex-direction: column;
    height: auto;
  }
}
  </pre>
</div>

